Title: Fuji road bike with accessories
text: I am selling a bike I don't have time to ride anymore. I bought the bike used and have used it for about 1 1/2 years. It is in excellent shape and has been well taken care of. It has an aluminum frame with carbon forks. Bike size is 61 cm. It shifts smoothly and has a Shimano 105 gear shifter. One tire has been recently replaced due to a flat. Recently tuned up and had handlebars wrapped with Gator tape. Also new gear shifting cables installed. The drop handlebars hurt my back so I installed a riser to make them higher. Also the narrow seat wasn't comfortable so I installed one a little wider. I still have the old seat and the handlebars can be restored to original setup if desired. A Swagman car carrier XC2 is included used with a  2" or 1 1/4" receiver hitch - can carry 2 bikes. There is a little bag under the seat that has all the necessary tools needed in case of a flat on the road - complete with compressed air canister. There is a bike lock included for stops along the route. A air pump for tires, box of extra inner tubes, front and rear lights, a phone holder, gloves and bike computer are included also. The package upgrades and accessories are worth over $800 but asking $600. You can text at 6 six 2 - two 6 zero - 89 six seven for more info. Price is firm!

Title: Yakima 4 Bike Tilt Out Hitch Rack with Integrated Locking System
text: This listing is for a Yakima 4 Bike Tilt Out Hitch Rack with Integrated Locking System. Rack natively fits 1 1/4" receivers. This listing also includes a CURT 45770 Trailer Hitch Receiver Adapter Reducer, 2" to 1 1/4" allowing the rack to work with both receiver sizes. There are two hitch locks one for the rack and one for the adapter. The rack itself has a cable lock made into one of the bike support arms that pulls out of one of the tubes to secure bikes to the rack. All straps and keys are present. I have used this rack behind a Honda Accord and an F150 and it works great on both vehicles.   I am located on the north side of Cullman, AL (i65 Exit 310). Title: 2003 Chevrolet Chevy Express 3500 11 Passenger Extended Van
text: Nice, well-taken care of 2003 Chevy Express 3500 Extended Van - 11 passenger seating with lots of extra cargo room.   This is the extended length version originally 15 passenger which had the 4-passenger seat at the back window. It served our growing family well, and we removed the rear seat to open up the large cargo area - room for big coolers/bins for shopping, or a few bikes for a trip to the park, or all the luggage space needed for a road trip. A 4-passenger seat can easily be found if you need that extra seat.   185k miles and still runs great , with newer good quality tires on it. The 3500 series has a strong engine for going up steep hills and passing when needed.

Title: 2002 BMW K1200RS
text: 2002 BMW K1200RS FOR SALE  I bought this bike from a close friend who bought the bike brand new in 2002. It had been sitting for a few years and I did some basic maintenance to get it going again. That maintenance included: fresh gas, new battery, topping off the brake fluid, and an oil change.  The bike currently has 20, 550 miles on it and they will slowly go up since I ride the bike around town and to work a few times a week.  The tires are old but still ride fine and it needs new grips.  There are some scratches on the right hand side fairing where the previous owner dropped the bike in his driveway but none of the mounting points are broken or cracked.  This bike is extremely heavy and really thrives at highway speeds.  I am 6 feet 3 inches tall and I weigh 240 pounds and I would say I fit this bike well.  It has a 6 speed transmission, heated grips, adjustable seat, locking detachable saddle bags, ABS, and cruise control.  The bike will also come with 2 keys and a tank bag.  I have put over 500 miles on this bike since I picked it up late last year and I really enjoy riding it however I prefer sport bikes and I am currently trying to downsize my current collection of vehicles.  All this bike really needs is some fresh rubber (tires & grips) and it could easily be rode across the country.  Asking $4200 OBO.  Cash Only.  Please don't waste my time.  Clean Alabama title in my name that I will sign over to you as soon as I have the full amount in cash in my hand.  No test rides unless I am holding full amount in cash in my hand.  Thanks for looking!  Cheers
